      <section eId="sec_580_711">
        <num>580-711</num>
        <heading>Modification of Convention child support order</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_580_711__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>A\ntribunal of this state may not modify a Convention child support order\nif the obligee remains a resident of the foreign country where the\nsupport order was issued unless:\n</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="sec_580_711__subsec_a__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>the obligee submits to the jurisdiction of a tribunal of this\nstate, either expressly or by defending on the merits of the case\nwithout objecting to the jurisdiction at the first available\nopportunity; or\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_580_711__subsec_a__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>the foreign tribunal lacks or refuses to exercise jurisdiction to\nmodify its support order or issue a new support order.\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_580_711__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>If a tribunal of this state does not modify a Convention child\nsupport order because the order is not recognized in this state,\nsubdivision</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_580_711__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>of section 580-708 of this part applies.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
